# Angular conventions

- Standalone components only; `imports: [...]` in `@Component`.
- Use `inject()` for DI; `protected readonly` for template API.
- Prefer signals/computed in stores (`FormStore`, `TableStore`) — match existing code.
- One component per folder: `.ts`, `.html`, `.scss` (`styleUrl`, `templateUrl`).
- Icons: import from `@lucide/angular` (same as form/table defs).
- Styling: use CSS variables from `styles.scss`; avoid hard-coded hex in components.
- No NgModules unless the codebase already uses them in that area.
- **No unit tests** — do not add or extend `*.spec.ts` / Vitest files (see `00-project.mdc`).

## Responsive layout

- Primary mobile breakpoint: **768px** (`max-width: 768px`).
- In component SCSS: `@use 'styles/breakpoints' as *;` then `@include below-md { ... }` (requires `stylePreprocessorOptions.includePaths: ["src"]` in `angular.json`).
- Layout padding: `--layout-padding-x`, `--layout-padding-x-mobile`, etc. in `styles.scss`.
- Prefer responsive rules in **core** form/table/shell components so feature pages inherit automatically; only add feature SCSS when a screen has a unique layout (e.g. review-step two-column grid).
- Form footers stack at **640px** (`form-footer.component.scss`); do not change without reason.
- Tables on mobile: card list via `DataTableComponent` `isMobileLayout` (`matchMedia` 768px) — see `tables.mdc`; do not add a second table/card UI on feature pages.
- Shell/layout mobile behavior: see `00-project.mdc` (hamburger, drawer, `SidebarService`).
- Portal page titles: use `PageTitleComponent` (`app-page-title`, `shared/ui/page-title/`) in portal page templates — see `page-title.mdc`. Portal create/edit forms also require `PageBackLinkComponent` above the title. Do not inline `<h1 class="page-title">` or add title/back rendering to shared form/table components.
